LOKOJA – The Alema of Warri Kingdom, Chief Emmanuel Oritsejolomi Uduaghan, and his wife, Chief Natasha Akpoti-Uduaghan, have announced the arrival of their new baby boy into the family. Akpoti-Uduaghan, who was a 2019 Kogi State Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) gubernatorial aspirant, disclosed this to SATURDAY INDEPENDENT on Saturday in a telephone message and said she gave birth to the baby boy last Wednesday. In a highly jubilant tone, Natasha Uduaghan, a candidate of the PDP for the forthcoming Kogi Central Senatorial election said “Myself and my husband, Chief Emmanuel Oritsejolomi Uduaghan are very happy for the blessing of a bouncing baby boy. “We thanked God Almighty for this blessing. We are full of gratitude and thanks to God. “To God be the glory. Our son was born three days ago. This is my son with my husband, Chief Emmanuel Oritsejolomi Uduaghan, Alema of Warri Kingdom,” she disclosed.